<H3><font color="Maroon">ALL ANGELS GUILD OF THE DEAF<br><hr size=2 color=navy></font></h3>
<table cellspacing=5 cellpadding=3 border=0>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Purpose</i></font></td>
	<td>Provides fellowship, education and networking opportunities for deaf Episcopalians. Works closely with other religious, governmental and non-profit organizations in advocating and assisting on concerns of deaf people.</td>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Contacts</i></font></td>
	<td><a href="mailto:poverino@aol.com">The Rev. Trenton Pitcher</a>, missioner (312) 243-9115</td>
</tr>
</table>

<H3><font color="Maroon">BISHOP'S ASSOCIATES<br><hr size=2 color=navy></font></h3>
<table cellspacing=5 cellpadding=3 border=0>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Purpose</i></font></td>
	<td>Supports the ministry of the Bishop of Chicago through sponsorship of educational and formational activities, through financial support and through nurturing new programs.</td>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Contacts</i></font></td>
	<td><a href="mailto:mstephenson@episcopalchicago.org">Michael Stephenson</a> (312) 751-6725</td>
</tr>
</table>

<H3><font color="Maroon">BROTHERHOOD OF ST. ANDREW<br><hr size=2 color=navy></font></h3>
<table cellspacing=5 cellpadding=3 border=0>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Purpose</i></font></td>
	<td>A ministry to men in the Episcopal Church and Anglican Communion, focusing on prayer, study and service. The Brotherhood of St. Andrew (BSA) was founded in the Diocese of Chicago in 1894, and held its first meeting in St. Andrew's Chapel at St. James Cathedral. The BSA's Chicago Assembly co-sponsors the annual youth recognition luncheon, and organizes the prayer vigil at Diocesan Convention. Additional events include an annual spring retreat and an annual assembly meeting in late fall.</td>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Contacts</i></font></td>
	<td>Ted Main, president, Chicago Assembly (630) 416-3952</td>
</tr>
</table>

<H3><font color="Maroon">CHICAGO EPISCOPAL CURSILLO<br><hr size=2 color=navy></font></h3>
<table cellspacing=5 cellpadding=3 border=0>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Purpose</i></font></td>
	<td>Conducts weekend Christian formational experiences and supports ongoing activities of the diocesan Cursillo community. Cursillo (Spanish for "short course") is a lay led program focusing on faith renewal and the building up of the faith community. It is centered around three-day weekend experiences featuring talks on nurturing relationship with God, Christian beliefs, and putting faith into practice. A key element is "The Fourth Day" program-the ongoing experience of workshops and reunion groups called Ultreas which provide guidance, support and fellowship to Cursillistas.</td>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Contacts</i></font></td>
	<td>Jeff Eng, lay director (312) 701-4918</td>
</tr>
</table>

<H3><font color="Maroon">DAUGHTERS OF THE KING<br><hr size=2 color=navy></font></h3>
<table cellspacing=5 cellpadding=3 border=0>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Purpose</i></font></td>
	<td>An order of lay and ordained women devoted to strengthening the spiritual life of congregations through prayer, service and evangelism.</td>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Contacts</i></font></td>
	<td>Lillian Gunnar, president, diocesan chapter (773) 338-4853</td>
</tr>
</table>

<H3><font color="Maroon">EPISCOPAL CHURCH WOMEN<br><hr size=2 color=navy></font></h3>
<table cellspacing=5 cellpadding=3 border=0>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Purpose</i></font></td>
	<td>Promotes the mission of the church and the ministry of women through training programs, outreach, fundraising and worship and fellowship. The diocesan ECW sponsors an endowment fund for promotional, educational and missionary work in the church; oversees United Thank Offering collections in the diocese; and operates a prison ministry to women incarcerated in correctional facilities.</td>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Contacts</i></font></td>
	<td>Laris Gross, president (312) 751-4200, <a href="mailto:ecw@episcopalchicago.org">ecw@episcopalchicago.org</a></td>
</tr>
</table>

<H3><font color="Maroon">EPISCOPAL MARRIAGE ENCOUNTER<br><hr size=2 color=navy></font></h3>
<table cellspacing=5 cellpadding=3 border=0>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Purpose</i></font></td>
	<td>A marriage enrichment program designed to help husbands and wives better understand each other and their relationship to God, and to deepen their love. The weekend experience is structured around a series of talks given by a lay couple and a clergy couple who speak about deepening their relationship with God, with their spouses and with the world.</td>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Contacts</i></font></td>
	<td>Dale and Debra Sands (847) 381-8353</td>
</tr>
</table>

<H3><font color="Maroon">INTEGRITY/CHICAGO<br><hr size=2 color=navy></font></h3>
<table cellspacing=5 cellpadding=3 border=0>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Purpose</i></font></td>
	<td>Advocacy organization for gay and lesbian Episcopalians in the Diocese of Chicago. Annual events include the Day of Prayer for People Living with HIV/AIDS, a fall banquet, and participation in Chicago's Gay Pride Parade.</td>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Contacts</i></font></td>
	<td>Bob Vogler (708) 383-3239</td>
</tr>
</table>

<H3><font color="Maroon">NATIONAL CATHEDRAL ASSOCIATION<br><hr size=2 color=navy></font></h3>
<table cellspacing=5 cellpadding=3 border=0>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Purpose</i></font></td>
	<td>Promotes through education and fundraising the mission of the Cathedral of SS. Peter and Paul in Washington D.C., otherwise known as Washington National Cathedral.</td>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Contacts</i></font></td>
	<td>Dorothy Laudati, diocesan chair (847) 491-1026</td>
</tr>
</table>

<H3><font color="Maroon">UNION OF BLACK EPISCOPALIANS<br><hr size=2 color=navy></font></h3>
<table cellspacing=5 cellpadding=3 border=0>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Purpose</i></font></td>
	<td><p>A confederation of 54 chapters and interest groups serving black Episocopalians throughout the United States and the Caribbean. Organized in 1968 as the Union of Black Clergy and Laity, and devoted to fighting racism by encouraging participation by black people in the total life of the church, and on every level through evangelism, communication, advocacy, referrals, ecumenical and interfaith cooperation, lobbying, resource development, and youth leadership development.</p>
		<p>The Chicago Chapter has provided two past presidents: The Very Rev. Richard Tolliver (1992-1995) rector of St. Edmund's, Chicago, and the Rev. Darryl James (1995-1998), rector of Messiah-St. Bartholomew, Chicago; the current secretary, Pat Simpson-Turner of St. Edmund's, Chicago, and a number of directors.</p>
	</td>
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#D3EEEF"><font face="Verdana"><i>Contacts</i></font></td>
	<td>Marcia Cambric, president, Chicago Chapter (773) 821-6983<br>
		<i>Mail</i>: Messiah-St. Bartholomew Episcopal Church, 8255 S. Dante, Chicago, IL 60619
	</td>
</tr>
</table>

